WEBVTT

00:07:28.680 --> 00:07:31.136
Habermas. Fernand Braudel.

00:07:31.160 --> 00:07:32.816
We were reading everything

00:07:32.840 --> 00:07:36.896
and we had to come to a conclusion
of how are we going to structure our work?

00:07:36.920 --> 00:07:38.776
So "O for the P," we called it,

00:07:38.800 --> 00:07:40.880
a preferential option for the poor.

00:07:41.560 --> 00:07:44.616
The most important thing
about a preferential option for the poor

00:07:44.640 --> 00:07:45.880
is what it's not.

00:07:46.360 --> 00:07:50.616
It's not a preferential option
for your own sense of heroism.

00:07:50.640 --> 00:07:52.096
It's not a preferential option

00:07:52.120 --> 00:07:55.696
for your own idea about
how to lift the poor out of poverty.

00:07:55.720 --> 00:07:58.616
It's not a preferential option
for your own organization.

00:07:58.640 --> 00:08:00.536
And the hardest of all,